# Foreign Key Relationship Testing Standards Rule

When creating tests for entities with foreign key relationships, ensure all three required test patterns are implemented to verify proper foreign key handling and navigation property updates.

## Required Test Patterns

### 1. Basic Foreign Key Update Test
- Test updating the foreign key property directly
- Verify the foreign key is updated in the database
- Ensure the foreign key value is correctly stored

### 2. Frontend Scenario Test
- Test updating with navigation properties loaded (using `Include()`)
- Simulate the exact frontend workflow
- Verify both foreign key and navigation property are updated
- Test the complete user interaction flow

### 3. Service Layer Test
- Test the service method specifically
- Ensure the service handles the update correctly
- Verify the Safe Update pattern is used properly

## Implementation Examples

### ✅ Good - Complete Test Suite for Foreign Key Relationships
```csharp
[TestFixture]
public class ViolationForeignKeyTests : TestBase
{
    [Test]
    public async Task UpdateViolationType_ShouldUpdateForeignKey()
    {
        // Arrange
        var violation = await CreateTestViolationAsync();
        var newViolationType = await CreateTestViolationTypeAsync();
        
        // Act - Basic Foreign Key Update Test
        violation.ViolationTypeId = newViolationType.Id;
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
        
        // Assert
        var updatedViolation = await _context.Violations
            .FirstAsync(v => v.Id == violation.Id);
        Assert.That(updatedViolation.ViolationTypeId, Is.EqualTo(newViolationType.Id));
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task UpdateViolationType_WithNavigationProperty_ShouldUpdateBoth()
    {
        // Arrange - Frontend Scenario Test
        var violation = await _context.Violations
            .Include(v => v.ViolationType)
            .FirstAsync();
        var newViolationType = await CreateTestViolationTypeAsync();
        
        // Act - Simulate frontend workflow
        violation.ViolationTypeId = newViolationType.Id;
        violation.ViolationType = newViolationType; // Navigation property update
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
        
        // Assert - Verify both foreign key and navigation property
        var updatedViolation = await _context.Violations
            .Include(v => v.ViolationType)
            .FirstAsync(v => v.Id == violation.Id);
        
        Assert.That(updatedViolation.ViolationTypeId, Is.EqualTo(newViolationType.Id));
        Assert.That(updatedViolation.ViolationType.Id, Is.EqualTo(newViolationType.Id));
    }

    [Test]
    public async Task ViolationService_UpdateViolationType_ShouldUseSafeUpdatePattern()
    {
        // Arrange - Service Layer Test
        var violationService = new ViolationService(_dbContextFactory);
        var violation = await CreateTestViolationAsync();
        var newViolationType = await CreateTestViolationTypeAsync();
        
        // Act - Test service method
        violation.ViolationTypeId = newViolationType.Id;
        await violationService.UpdateViolationAsync(violation);
        
        // Assert - Verify service handled update correctly
        var updatedViolation = await _context.Violations
            .Include(v => v.ViolationType)
            .FirstAsync(v => v.Id == violation.Id);
        
        Assert.That(updatedViolation.ViolationTypeId, Is.EqualTo(newViolationType.Id));
        Assert.That(updatedViolation.ViolationType.Id, Is.EqualTo(newViolationType.Id));
    }
}
```

### ❌ Bad - Incomplete Test Coverage
```csharp
[Test]
public async Task UpdateViolationType_ShouldUpdateForeignKey()
{
    // ❌ Bad - Only tests basic foreign key update
    // Missing frontend scenario and service layer tests
    
    var violation = await CreateTestViolationAsync();
    var newViolationType = await CreateTestViolationTypeAsync();
    
    violation.ViolationTypeId = newViolationType.Id;
    await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    
    var updatedViolation = await _context.Violations
        .FirstAsync(v => v.Id == violation.Id);
    Assert.That(updatedViolation.ViolationTypeId, Is.EqualTo(newViolationType.Id));
}
```

### ❌ Bad - Missing Navigation Property Testing
```csharp
[Test]
public async Task UpdateViolationType_ShouldUpdateForeignKey()
{
    // ❌ Bad - Doesn't test navigation properties
    // Missing Include() and navigation property verification
    
    var violation = await CreateTestViolationAsync();
    var newViolationType = await CreateTestViolationTypeAsync();
    
    violation.ViolationTypeId = newViolationType.Id;
    await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    
    // Missing navigation property verification
    var updatedViolation = await _context.Violations
        .FirstAsync(v => v.Id == violation.Id);
    Assert.That(updatedViolation.ViolationTypeId, Is.EqualTo(newViolationType.Id));
}
```

