## Validation Checklist
- [ ] Basic foreign key update test implemented
- [ ] Frontend scenario test with Include() implemented
- [ ] Service layer test implemented
- [ ] Navigation properties are properly tested
- [ ] Foreign key values are verified in database
- [ ] Safe Update pattern is tested in service layer
- [ ] All three test patterns are present for each foreign key relationship

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
1. Testing only foreign key property without navigation properties
2. Missing Include() in frontend scenario tests
3. Not testing service layer methods
4. Skipping navigation property verification
5. Testing only one aspect of foreign key relationships
6. Not simulating real frontend workflows

## Benefits of Complete Test Coverage
- Ensures foreign keys are properly updated
- Verifies navigation properties work correctly
- Tests the complete user workflow
- Validates service layer implementation
- Prevents EF change tracking issues
- Ensures data consistency

This rule ensures comprehensive testing of foreign key relationships following the established testing standards.
